FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_CVRNAn exotic grotto has been discovered, and restricted planning permission grants you the opportunity to create a unique park in this hollowed out habitat! Building above the cavern is strictly prohibited, and guest numbers are limited, so you’ll need to conquer the depths to ensure this venture is a success. FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_NOMOYou'll need to be at the top of your game for this one! The former owners have abandoned this park and left it in a real mess; negative cash reserves, a huge loan to pay off, ludicrous layout, and some seriously inefficient amusement rides. If you can turn this around it'll be a miracle. FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_WNTRIt’s time to unwrap our plans for a festive-themed park in this jolly location. Just remember that your cash is a loan, not a gift! Spruce up your winter wonderland with seasonal scenery and draw in the merry crowds from far around. FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_PHD1Chief Beef's Raceway was built on the site of an old seafront racetrack to take advantage of the site's heritage. Unfortunately, money issues arose during construction and concessions had to be made, and the resulting track has been deemed a disappointment by the public. Can you realise the site’s full potential? FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_PHD2This park has been thrilling the public for over a century, but it’s starting to be eclipsed by the towering, twisting thrill machines of newer parks. The board is keen to reinvigorate it with some exciting, modern rides while preserving its heritage. Are you up to the challenge? FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_PHD3Downtown Park was supposed to bring a little happiness to this notorious neighbourhood, where security guards demand higher salaries because of the increased risk, but the founder’s ambitions were undermined by the high levels of crime. Can you succeed where they failed, and bring some joy to the area? FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_DINEMiss Elly's Diner has some great facilities, including a big wooden coaster for a spot of excitement! But its remote location means it doesn’t see many visitors, and its potential isn’t being realised. Can you build on this location and draw in the crowds? FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_MARSThey filmed some pretty famous movies out here in the desert. It kind of looks like Mars, don’t it. The place isn’t much in demand any more – it’s all CGI these days – but the company doesn’t want to let it go. They want you to turn it into a theme park instead! FrontEndMenu_ScenarioDetails_MINESome poor fella bought this mine from a prospector, and took out some big loans to pay for it. Turns out it was a scam. The varmint had salted the mine! Now he’s trying to turn it into a tourist attraction with some fireworks he was given and Old West-style streets, but it’s not doing as well as he hoped and he needs your help. Coaster_BoltBolt Coaster_Bolt_DescShuttle roller coaster, allowing the train to travel forwards to an end point before then travelling along the track in reverse back to the station. Coaster_DegenDegen Coaster_Degen_DescSpecially designed for inversions. Coaster_GnarlerGnarler Coaster_Gnarler_DescA traditional rollercoaster type that's primarily made of wood, which results in an exciting, rough and wild ride. This variant uses a more modern car compared to 'The Monster' Wooden Coaster. Coaster_PowerUpPower Up Coaster_PowerUp_DescA coaster where the train is chain-lifted vertically before then being inverted, which can also pass through the station multiple times. Coaster_SteelVengeanceSteel Vengeance Coaster_SteelVengeance_DescOfficial track of Cedar Point's Steel Vengeance coaster. Steel track and wooden coaster supports combine to create a hybrid coaster that can invert, whilst retaining the look and characteristics of a wooden coaster. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_EasyEasy staff setting: • Staff building perks have a greater effect. • Staff can quit at a lower happiness level. • Staff start at a higher happiness value. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_ApatheticWhen Entertainers are set to Apathetic:
• Entertainers don't increase guest happiness as much as normal. • Entertainers can entertain less guests at once. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_CommercialWhen Entertainers are set to Commercial:
• Entertainers don't increase guest happiness as much as normal. • Entertainers can entertain more guests at once. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_DefaultWhen Entertainers are set to default:
• Normal happiness increase for guests. • Normal Time between performances. • Normal amount of guests per performance. • Normal workload levels before Entertainers get stressed. • Normal pay and energy levels. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_EasyWhen Entertainers are set to easy:
• Entertainers increase guest happiness more than normal. • Entertainers can perform more regularly. • Entertainers can handle more workloads. • Entertainers don't tire as quickly. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_EnergeticWhen Entertainers are set to Energetic:
• Entertainers lose energy at a decreased rate. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_EntitledWhen Entertainers are set to entitled:
• Entertainers require more money to keep them happy. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_FatiguedWhen Entertainers are set to Fatigued:
• Entertainers lose energy at an increased rate. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_GratefulWhen Entertainers are set to Grateful:
• Entertainers require less money to keep them happy. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_HardWhen Entertainers are set to hard:
• Entertainers don't increase guest happiness as much as normal. • Entertainers have a longer delay between performances. • Entertainers get overworked from lower workloads. • Entertainers get tired faster. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_LazyWhen Entertainers are set to lazy:
• Entertainers don't increase happiness of guests as much. • Entertainers have a larger gap between performances. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_PassionateWhen Entertainers are set to passionate:
• Entertainers increase guest happiness more than normal. • Entertainers can entertain more guests at once. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_Entertainer_StressedWhen Entertainers are set to get easily stressed:
• Entertainers get overworked from smaller workloads. ScenarioEditor_Staff_ProfileDescription_HardHard staff setting: • Staff building perks have a reduced effect. • Staff can quit at a higher happiness level. • Staff start at lower happiness.
